summary:
Experienced Chemistry and Biology Teacher with a demonstrated history of working in the education management industry. Skilled in Science Education, STEM, Pastoral Counselling, First Aid in Mental Health, Pastoral Care, Lab Techniques and Apple Certified. 

Strong research professional with a Bachelors focused in Biological Sciences and Chemistry with Teacher Education from University of Limerick. 

Have a range of experience with different curricula including International Baccalaureate (Middle Years Programme and Diploma Programme) and UK GCSE and A-Level. 

Currently a Pastoral Lead working alongside the Senior Leadership team as a Housemistress and Head of Year. Role includes monitoring behaviour and academic progress of students in Year 11.
